locations.title: Meteor House
locations.description: This cabin has a hole in the roof where a meteorite has come through and killed the inhabitants.  The room is smoking and the bodies are burned.  Inside you can collect the meteorite.

locations.title: Strange Statues Cave
locations.description:
**Puzzle:** Each statue has a certain number of fingers. You need to push the buttons on the statues that have the number of fingers: 2, 3, 5 and 7 (prime numbers). 

One of the statues is missing an arm, which can can be found in a pile of rocks in the corner of the cave. This statue will represent 7. If you accidentally press a button on an incorrect statue, you can push the button back out by pressing the button from the back of the statue. The order that you select does not matter. It's hard to see this button, so use Eagle Eye and first person view.

**Reward:** 3 x Gold Bar (3 x $500)

locations.title: Strange Statues - Painting
locations.description:
This area has a big rock formation with a hole in the middle of it.  Head into the circular opening in the big rock to inspect a painting.

Then head to the Strange Statuues - Cave location to earn $1500

locations.title: Giant Remains (Sasquatch Skeleton)
locations.description: Follow the path south-east.  The skeleton is under a large overhanging rock.

locations.title: Tiny Church
locations.description: A tiny church for a tiny congregation

locations.title: Face in Cliff
locations.description:
A Mount Rushmore-esque face carved into the mountain. Approach from the rear to make it to the top. 

The sculptor has hung himself from and left a note which you can retrieve from his body - "Note from the Sculptor"

locations.title: Crashed Airship
locations.description:
The wreckage of a flying machine.
This is likely Charles from Red Dead Redemption 1 (who you see crashing, after helping him build his airship).

locations.title: Manmade Mutant
locations.description: A gruesome frankenstein experiment, made from various animal parts.

locations.description: On a rock ledge, just above the train tracks

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Chez Porter
locations.description:
**Requirements**: Chapter 2

Climb up a ladder inside the barn to the above floor to find the stash box next to some hay stacks. The treasure box contains 2 x $50 and a jewelry bag. Be sure to loot everything else in the houses too.

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Aberdeen Pig Farm
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Chapter 2

When you arrive at the farm, there's a guy sitting on the porch who greets you. Greet him back, talk to him and follow him inside his house. Then rob the place. Also be sure to go back outside and enter the door at the southern side of the house. This lets you in the room with the stash. This door is closed until you have followed the guy inside his house. It’s a little lockbox with 2 x $20 inside, be sure to loot that alongside everything else in the house.

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Lonnie's Shack
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Chapter 2

Inside Lonnie's Shack there are 4 guys. Kill 3 of them but keep 1 alive. Aim your gun at the last surviving guy and threaten him. Then he tells you the location of the stash. This will be different depending on who is the last guy alive.

**Important**: Make a manual save beforehand.  If you don't interrogate the last guy, you can't pick up the stash.

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Van Horn Mansion
locations.description: Go here early in the game to find two residents inside. Enter at night time and you'll find two people sleeping on the lower floor. Steal the money from their table and loot everything else in the house.

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Catfish Jacksons
locations.description: There's either a dad and his son inside or just the son. You can get the shotgun from the living room and threaten the son so he tells you the stash location. It's outside of the house, on the side to the right of the entrance. There’s a little hole on the side of the house with a crate inside. Loot the crate and be sure to loot everything inside as well, especially the Premium Cigarette Packs in the chest of the son's room and the shotgun from living room.

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Watson's Cabin
locations.description:
In Watson's Cabin you find an old lady. Enter her house and use the ladder in the back to climb down into the cellar. Steal her shotgun and leave. Return to the cabin the next day and you'll encounter the 4 sons of the old lady. Kill them all and a lockbox will now be available on the kitchen table that was previously not there. The lockbox is the secret stash and contains 1 x $73.  

**Bonus:** Check the nightstand drawer for a Gold Earring.

locations.title: Homestead Stash - Wilard's Rest
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Available after completing the first story mission in Chapter 6

Talk to the resident here and teach her how to hunt. Return 2 days later. When you return, have a shooting contest with her and then you can loot her lockbox. Be sure to loot everything else too.

locations.title: Shop Robbery: Rhodes Gunsmith
locations.description:
Talk to the trapped man through the basement window of the Gunsmith. Once he tells you his story, you can hold up the owner of the store and make him take you to the basement.  

From there you can loot the room, free the man, and find a **Lancaster Repeater**.

locations.title: Shop Robbery: Strawberry General Store
locations.description:
Have a look through the basement window before entering the store. Afterwards, head inside and hold up the owner to make him open the trapdoor to the basement. If you threaten him further, he'll show you a loose brick in the wall.  

Inspect the brick and loot the basement to complete the robbery.

locations.title: Robbery: Saint Denis Gunsmith
locations.description:
There's a security door inside the gunsmith that you should knock on before holding up the owner. Once he opens the door for you, kill the guard on the other side and go to the top floor of the building. You'll find an illegal poker room to loot, as well as a secret safe that the players will show you if you threaten them.  

Bonus points if you can complete the robbery without a single shot fired!

locations.title: Robbery: Valentine Doctor
locations.description: You can knock on the door either at the back of the building or inside the doctor's surgery before holding up the doctor and forcing him to open the back room. Try to escape quickly to avoid a large bounty, but don't forget the money and the **Schofield Revolver**.

locations.title: Coach Robbery: Hector (I, II & III)
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Complete *Friends in Very Low Places* (Chapter 3)  

Hector is a clerk in Strawberry post office who will give you a total of 3 coach robbery missions. Buy the information from him and read the notes in your satchel to find mission details and the coach locations.  

Stolen coaches can be taken to the wagon fence at Emerald Ranch.

locations.title: Coach Robbery: Alden (I, II & III)
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Complete *Friends in Very Low Places* (Chapter 3)  

Alden is a clerk in Rhodes post office who will give you a total of 3 coach robbery missions. Buy the information from him and read the notes in your satchel to find mission details and the coach locations.  

Stolen coaches can be taken to the wagon fence at Emerald Ranch.

locations.description:
Approach the island from the peninsula on the western side to avoid drowning. Swim to the small island in the middle of the lake and inspect the bushes. The treasure is hidden under a rock.  

**Treasure:** Gold Bar x 2

locations.title: Poisonous Trail Treasure
locations.description:
**NB: You'll need to bring a lantern to see inside the cave.**

Walk through the waterfall to find the secret cave. Climb over the first ledge, and drop down the steep drop. Look for another steep path to the right, and head down it.  If you come to a massive chamber with natural light breaking through, you've gone too far.

You'll come to a small triangular tunnel entrance that you have to crouch to go through.  Take the right-hand path after going through.  When this chamber opens up, you'll see a ledge that you need to run and jump off. You'll land below it, and then you can climb up one last ledge and search for a boulder to find 4 x gold bars ($500).

locations.title: Poisonous Trail Treasure Hunt - Start
locations.description:
**Requirements:** You need to start "The Noblest of Men, and a Woman" side quest.

You need to kill Flaco Hernandez, and then search his cabin to find the **Poisonous Trail Map 1**.

locations.title: High Stakes Treasure
locations.description: When facing the river, take the left path along the cliff edge.  You'll pass a Rock Carving on the way.  Take the path above it.  You'll then need to jump down a gap.  And then fall down once more (you'll take damage this time).  Then crawl under a nearby ledge, and there you'l find 3 x gold bars ($500 each)

locations.title: High Stakes Treasure Hunter
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Complete The New South in Chapter 3

To find the **High Stakes Treasure Map 1**, you'll need to randomly encounter a treasure hunter and take the map from him.  There are roughly ~8 different potential spawn points around the New Hampshire area.  Image coming soon  

**Note:** If you fail to recover the map from him on 3 separate occasions, it will become available for purchase at a Fence.

locations.title: Random Event: Ku Klux Klan Meeting
locations.description:
Here you can stumble across a comedic KKK meeting.  

If you get close enough, they might attack you.  Killing and looting the dark robed Klansman gives you a "Meeting Notes" letter

locations.title: Arm Amputation
locations.description:
**Random Event Time:** Unknown

A man on a horse will call for help and then fall off.  He'll ask you to take him to the doctor in Saint Denis. If you do this you'll see the doctor amputate his arm.

locations.title: Ghost of Agnes Dowd
locations.description:
**Available:** Between 9pm - 3am, only when it's foggy. 

**Interaction:** Sometimes she will appear as a white ghost, other times she will be invisible. She spawns in this area and can be heard crying. Use your binoculars to see her, as she will fade away if you get too close.  

You can encounter this event 16 times, with 2 days between each encounter.  Each time she will have unique dialog.  After the 16th time she won't spawn again.

locations.title: Cave Hermit
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** There are 5 possible stages, each available at least 3 in-game days after the previous one. You'll need to stay in his presence long enough to hear all the man has to say (and to actually see him), even if he asks you to go away.

locations.title: Blind Man Cassidy (I)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** This mystical blind man will tell fortunes if given a dollar. **He is available in many different locations and at any time.** You must wait 3 in-game days to trigger a new meeting after each encounter, with 18 potential stages to experience before Chapter 6. Reaching the Epilogue will give you a further 8 stages.

locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** The hermit will shoot to kill if he sees a trespasser. If you take him out, you can loot his house for collectibles and get his rare shotgun.

locations.title: Poor Joe
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** Poor Joe lives in a tree near the edge of the map. There are three stages of interaction, and you must wait at least 3 in-game days between each one. The final interaction is only available from Epilogue 1 onward.

locations.title: Giant
locations.description:
**Availablity:** Chapter 2 onward - between 8AM & 8PM  

**Interaction:** To unlock this character, you need to have studied at least 30 animal species. Head to the western shore of the river directly east of Wapiti Indian Reservation on a **clear day** (not rainy, stormy, snowy or foggy). A flock of birds will fly away on your arrival. Follow them on horseback to reach the giant's den. There are 2 conversations to be had with the giant, with at least 3 in-game days between them.

locations.description:
**Availability:**  Chapter 2 onward  - multiple locations. Note the Rhodes location is locked while the *No Good Deed* stranger mission is open.  

**Interaction:** This man can appear at 3 different locations throughout the game, and a further 4 locations from Epilogue 1 onward. He is searching for his friend Gavin. Looting him will give you the *Letter to Nigel from Tom*, which will help you to understand his story.

locations.title: Captain Russell
locations.description:
**Availability:**  Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:**  There are 3 stages to experience, with 3 in-game days between each one. 2 additional stages are unlocked from Epilogue 1 onward.

locations.title: Chelonian Master
locations.description:
**Availability:**  Complete Epilogue 2

**Interaction:**  The leader of a cult that worships turtles can be seen jumping off a cliff with his followers.

locations.title: Dr. Macintosh
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** By accepting the doctor's book and returning at least 3 in-game days later, you unlock a second interaction.

locations.title: Thomas Downes
locations.description:
**Availability:** Between the beginning of Chapter 2 and *Sodom? Back to Gomorrah* (Chapter 3)  

**Interaction:** There are 2 different conversations to experience: one before completing *Americans at Rest* (Chapter 2), and one after.

locations.title: Jon
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward - between 12PM & 6AM  

**Interaction:** This guy can be seen ranting in Valentine's Smithfields saloon. If you stay close, he will eventually attack you. Knock him out to pick up his raccoon mountain hat.

locations.title: Constipated Man
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2, after completing *Polite Society, Valentine Style*  

**Interaction:** A constipated man can be heard struggling inside room 2A at the hotel in Valentine.

locations.title: Nicholas Timmins
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward - between 8AM & 8PM  

**Interaction:**  Nicholas Timmins, the mayor of Strawberry, is welcoming people to his town. 3 interactions can be triggered (the first 2 at the Welcome Center, the 3rd in the main street), with at least 2 in-game days between them.

locations.title: Reverend
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward - between 8AM & 7PM  

**Interaction:** After your initial encounter, you can meet him again if you come back at least 24 in-game hours later.

locations.title: Homeless Vet Mickey (I)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** This guy asks for money at **2 possible spots** in Valentine. There are 6 stages of interaction, with a minimum of 3 in-game days between each one. A 7th stage is unlocked from Epilogue 1 onward.

locations.title: Homeless Vet Mickey (II)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** This guy asks for money at **2 possible spots** in Valentine. There are 6 stages of interaction, with a minimum of 3 in-game days between each one. A 7th stage is unlocked from Epilogue 1 onward.

locations.title: Dorothea
locations.description:
**Availability:** From Chapter 2 onward - between 8AM & 6PM  

**Interaction:** A suffragette who appears in Saint Denis. AFter your first encounter, you can experience a second one by coming back at least 1 in-game day later.

locations.title: Anders Helgerson
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward - between 8AM & 6PM  

**Interaction:**A recruiter for the Chelonian Cult, Anders will offer you a pamphlet if you talk to him.

locations.title: Eugenics Proponent
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward - between 8AM & 6PM  

**Interaction:** If you accept a pamphlet from this man, a cutscene ensues. He will run away from you at the next encounter (which is available 1 in-game day after the first).

locations.title: Timothy Donahue
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** This guy sells a book - *Get Rich Quick* - for $50. If you come back at least 2 in-game days later, you can demand a refund - though you will have to chase him down and loot him for it.

locations.title: Lillian Powell
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward - between 9AM & 9PM  

**Interaction:** A drunk, aging writer in the Saint Denis saloon. There are 4 stages to experience, each one 3 in-game days after the last.

locations.title: Sonny
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** This creepy guy lives in a cabin in the Bayou Nwa. If you accept his invitation to come inside, you will wake up in the wilderness with some of your money missing and your cores exhausted. Although, returning to the cabin and getting your revenge can be profitable.

locations.title: Joe Butler
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** Joe can be found begging outsides Rhodes General Store. There are initially 3 stages of interaction, with 3 in-game days between them. A 4th one is unlocked from Epilogue 1 onward.

locations.title: Soothsayer (I)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** An old and near-blind woman tells fortunes in exchange for money. There are 15 interaction stages, with 3 in-game days between them and **her location alternating between the Bayou and Bluewater Marsh,** The first 10 interactions can be triggered between Chapters 2 - 6, and the last 5 once you begin Epilogue 1.

locations.title: Soothsayer (II)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Chapter 2 onward  

**Interaction:** An old and near-blind woman tells fortunes in exchange for money. There are 15 interaction stages, with 3 in-game days between them and **her location alternating between the Bayou and Bluewater Marsh,** The first 10 interactions can be triggered between Chapters 2 - 6, and the last 5 once you begin Epilogue 1.

locations.title: Armadillo Town Crier (I)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Epilogue 1 onward - between 8AM & 7PM  

**Interaction:** This guy appears in two spots in Armadillo, warning you about a cholera outbreak.

locations.title: Armadillo Town Crier (II)
locations.description:
**Availability:** Epilogue 1 onward - between 8AM & 7PM  

**Interaction:** This guy appears in two spots in Armadillo, warning you about a cholera outbreak.

locations.title: Castor's Ridge Homestead
locations.description: **Interaction:** Here you'll find a man and his sons building a house. Return here frequently to receive small side quests from them. There are 4 stages in total.

locations.title: Appleseed Timber
locations.description:
A small lumber camp in the forest.

**Availability:** Until chapter 6  

**Interaction:** There are 3 stages to this event. Speak to the foreman to begin the 1st stage.

locations.title: Central Union Railroad
locations.description:
**Availability:** Until the first part of the epilogue

**Interaction:** There are 3 stages to experience.  Note that the camp will move slightly north-west as the stages progress

locations.title: Valentine Hotel Robbery - Room 1B
locations.description:
A stranger here will tell you that his friend double-crossed him, and he wants to get him back.  You'll need to rob the friend's room (1B, bottom floor, opposite the baths) in the nearby Valentine Hotel.  You'll find $50 there, and you'll have the option to split the money with the stranger, or break your word and keep all $50.

**NB:** Some users have mentioned that they cannot find any loot inside the hotel room.  It's unknown if this is a bug or not.

locations.title: Fundraiser
locations.description:

locations.title: American Dream
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Find the 3 Serial Killer Clues, and piece together the map.

**SPOILERS:** Once you piece together the map, enter through the locked basement door beside the cabin.  Then, inspect a knife stuck in the wall. You will then be attacked by the Stranger, Edward Lowry Jr.

locations.title: The American Inferno, Burnt Out
locations.description: **Requirements:** Complete *The Landowning Classes* (Epilogue 1)

locations.title: Horseshoe Overlook Camp
locations.description: This is your campsite until the end of Chapter 2.

locations.title: Clemens Point Camp
locations.description: This is your campsite for Chapter 3.

locations.title: Bonnie MacFarlane's Husband
locations.description: Along the shore, beside an overturned fishing boat, you'll find Bonnie MacFarlane's almost dead husband.  He'll hand you the **Lost Letter to Bonnie** before dying.

locations.title: Braithwaite's Secret
locations.description: A creepy exorcist-style woman. You'll find her locked in an outhouse here.

locations.title: UFO
locations.description: Inspect the Mysterious Sermon found inside the shack.  You'll then need to return at 2am and look up through the roof to see the UFO/Northern Lights

locations.title: Nite Folk Victim
locations.description:
Come here at night, and find a man hung from a tree at the side of the road. After approaching the body, you'll be attacked by 3 "Night Folk".

After killing them, shoot down the body and loot it to find the "Nite Folk's Victim's Note"

locations.title: Witch's Cauldron
locations.description: A small hut with a cauldron inside.  If you drink the **Mysterious Liquid**, you will be knocked out and wake up later.

locations.title: Nite Folk: Crying Woman
locations.description: Try wandering the area at night, and you might hear a crying woman.  If you approach her, she'll attack and run away. If you chase her you'll be attacked by a group of Nite Folk

locations.title: Robot
locations.description:
**Requirements: ** Complete chapter 4 mission "Joys of Civilization", Complete Marko Dragic stranger missions

If you're using the Electric Lantern, it will glow red/orange as you get closer to the robot

locations.title: Conversation with Bigfoot
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Study at least 30 animals

When you arrive at the location, a flock of birds will take off from the shore.  Follow them until you reach an inaccessible cave. A conversation with Bigfoot will automatically start.

You can have a second conversation if you return 3 days later.

locations.title: Ghost Train
locations.description: Spawns on this stretch of tracks, generally in the middle of the night.

locations.title: Vampire
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Find the 5 vampire clues

After finding the 5 clues, you'll find a vampire here finishing off his latest victim.  If you kill him, you'll receive an Ornate Dagger

Note: You have to come at night, and he may not always spawn.

locations.title: Mexico Glitch
locations.description:
**Requirements:** Max horse stamina, stamina + health stimulants & revivers.

**Note:** Save before attempting this glitch.

First, you need to cross the river at the narrowest point, opposite this marker.  Your horse will need stamina + health stimulants to stay alive during this.

Then, head for this marked location.  You need to run your horse into the end of the canyon, and attempt to glitch yourself up to the top ledge (you can use cheats if your horse dies - but make sure you save before doing this).

Eventually you'll be able to glitch yourself up on top of the canyon and explore all of Mexico.

locations.title: Glowing Pentagram
locations.description: A red glowing pentagram appears below a small shack here between 4am and 5am

locations.title: Faded Letter
locations.description:
**Location:** Under a tree in a lock box.  
**Description:** Letter to Douglas Gray from Lucille Braithwaite

locations.title: Mysterious Aztec Writing
locations.description: **Location:** In the alleyway, on the wall

locations.title: Sheep Lover
locations.description: You'll find a Gold Wedding Ring tied to his "wife"

locations.title: Serial Killer Clue - #2
locations.description:
**Murder Scene:** A dismembered body is tied to a rock. On a nearby rock you'll find a head with "Killer Clue 2 Piece" in its mouth.  

**Mission Unlocked:** Finding all 3 clues unlocks the *American Dreams* stranger mission.

locations.title: Serial Killer Clue - #1
locations.description:
**Murder Scene:** A dismembered body is strung up under a bridge. On a stake nearby you'll find "Killer Clue 1 Piece". You can also shoot the body down.  

**Mission Unlocked:** Finding all 3 clues unlocks the *American Dreams* stranger mission.

locations.title: Serial Killer Clue - #3
locations.description:
**Murder Scene:** This body is tied to a large tree. At the base of the tree, you'll find a head on a stake, with "Serial Killer 3 Piece" in it's mouth.  

**Mission Unlocked:** Finding all 3 clues unlocks the *American Dreams* stranger mission.

locations.title: Massive Dead Snake
locations.description: There's a large dead snake in a tree here. Not sure what it does yet....

locations.title: Vampire Clue - #1
locations.description: The clue is above, on the wall on the corner of the building.  You'll see white writing which you need to examine.

locations.title: Vampire Clue - #2
locations.description: Just before you enter the marker, look to the right of the arch, and you'll see an area with some railings an a metal gate.  The clue is here, on the wall on the left (beside some barrels).

locations.title: Vampire Clue - #3
locations.description: Between the General Store and the Butcher's.The writing is on the wall facing the southern road.

locations.title: Vampire Clue - #4
locations.description: The writing is a above a chair, on the corner.

locations.title: Vampire Clue - #5
locations.description: On a wall under the arches.  This clue is slightly difficult to spot, due to the shadows.

locations.title: Del Lobo Execution
locations.description:
**Availability:** Epilogue 1 onward  

A deputy turns in a Del Lobo in Tumbleweed and the Sheriff executes the outlaw.  

**Mission Unlocked:** Two bounty hunter missions - *Joaquin Arroyo* & *Esteban Cortez*
